main event: A witness observed a circular, disc-shaped object with a stubby vapor trail in Tiffin, Ohio on May 17, 1965.
interesting points: The sighting lasted approximately 1 minute and 20 seconds,The object was silver in color and estimated to be traveling at 1,200 m.p.h.,The witness reported seeing similar objects on several occasions prior to this sighting,The object went out of sight and did not make any sound,The sighting prompted an investigation by the U.S. Air Force, concluding it was likely an aircraft.
sighted object: a circular, disc-shaped object with a short, stubby, horizontal vapor trail
